This paper is primarily focused on the navigation of robots in dynamic environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of Kalman filters for uncertainty reduction, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions path generation and curvature checks, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG).
